{
  "text": "Proteins resolved by electrophoresis on 10% -15% sodium dodecyl sulfate polyacrylamide gels were then transferred to Hybond-P polyvinylidene difluoride membranes (GE Healthcare, Little Chalfont, Buckinghamshire, UK). Non-specific binding on blots was blocked with 5% nonfat dry milk in TBS-T (Tris-buffered saline containing 0.1% Tween-20, pH 7.4) at room temperature for 30 min. The primary antibodies were: rat anti-HMGB1 mAb [CITATION_1] CA, USA), and rabbit or mouse IgG (GE Healthcare). Immunoreactive bands on blots were visualized using ECL Plus enhanced chemiluminescence substrates (GE Healthcare). Bands were quantified using Image J (National Institutes of Health, Bethesda, MD, USA).",
